function longestSquareStreak(nums) {
    const numSet = new Set(nums);
    let longestStreak = -1;

    for (const num of numSet) {
        let streak = 1;

        while (numSet.has(Math.sqrt(num))) {
            streak++;
            num = Math.sqrt(num);
        }

        longestStreak = Math.max(longestStreak, streak);
    }

    return longestStreak >= 2 ? longestStreak : -1;
}
```

    The algorithm for finding the longest square streak consists of the following steps:

1. Create a set of unique numbers from the given array. This will help in eliminating duplicate numbers.
2. Initialize a variable 'longestStreak' to store the length of the longest square streak found so far. Set it to -1 initially.
3. Iterate through each unique number in the set.
4. For each number, start a streak count at 1.
5. Check if the square root of the current number is present in the set. If it is, increment the streak count and update the current number in the streak to the square root of the current number.
6. Repeat step 5 until the square root of the current number is not found in the set.
7. Update the longest streak found so far by comparing it with the current streak.
8. After iterating through all unique numbers, check if the longest streak is at least 2. If it is, return the length of the longest streak. Otherwise, return -1.

